Finding The Titanic: A Cold War Secrecy

#Titanic #ColdWarSecrets #History #FindingTheTitanic #InterestingHistory

When Bob Ballard revealed the Titanic's resting place in 1985, it stirred global interest. However, beneath the waves lay an even more gripping tale. Unbeknownst to many, Ballard was commissioned by the U.S. government for a secret mission. His task: to investigate the conditions of two sunken nuclear submarines from the 60s. Ensuring this clandestine operation remained under wraps was crucial, so what better cover story than the hunt for the legendary Titanic? Having completed his covert mission successfully, Ballard and his team allocated their leftover time to the Titanic search, ultimately revealing the ship's hauntingly beautiful wreckage to the world.
